    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="987"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d987">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.Os4/122a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>772. We are arranging for turning over archives at Mexico City to diplomatic
                    representative of another nation but arrangements <pb facs="0753" n="637"
                        xml:id="pg_637"/> not yet complete. Hope you can remain until instructions
                    can be given. If, however, your safety requires earlier departure, leave Embassy
                    in charge of clerk until instructions can be sent. Say to Consul Shanklin and
                    other consuls that they may leave whenever in their judgment safety requires.
                    Instructions will be sent consulates direct as soon as arrangements can be made
                    for care of records.</p>
                <p>Mexican Chargé has just asked for passports and they are being prepared. Please
                    report on Americans there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
